<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

    <PropertyGroup>
        <ImplicitUsings>disable</ImplicitUsings>
        <TargetFrameworks>net8.0;netstandard2.0;netstandard2.1;net9.0</TargetFrameworks>
        <GeneratePackageOnBuild>true</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
        <Title>CliRunner</Title>
        <Authors>AlastairLundy</Authors>
        <Description>CliRunner is a library for interacting with Command Line Interfaces,</Description>
        <Copyright>Copyright (c) Alastair Lundy 2024</Copyright>
        <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/alastairlundy/CliRunner</RepositoryUrl>
        <RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
        <IncludeSymbols>true</IncludeSymbols>
        <SymbolPackageFormat>snupkg</SymbolPackageFormat>
        <PackageReleaseNotes>## Changes since 0.3.0

### Additions
* Added xml doc comments to ``ArgumentsBuilder``, ``CredentialsBuilder``, and ``EnvironmentVariablesBuilder``  builder classes
* Added xml doc comments to ``CommandResultValidation``, ``CommandResult``, ``CommandPiping``, and ``BufferedCommandResult`` classes.
* Added .NET 9 TFM to CliRunner
* Added .NET Standard 2.0 support to CliRunner.Specializations library


### General Changes
* Renamed Command class' ``RequiresAdministrator`` method to ``RunAsAdministrator``
* Renamed Command class' ``RunAsAdministrator`` property to ``RequiresAdministrator``
* Implement IDisposable in ``CredentialsBuilder``
* Enhanced ``CommandNotSuccessfulException`` exception information.
* Removed code that prevented an Exception being thrown when ``UseShellExecute`` was set to true and ``StandardInput`` was not set to Null - This is intended behaviour by .NET and the workaround is being removed


### Removals
* Removed ``UrlRunner`` and ``IUrlRunner`` - URL Opening code is being moved to a separate library that'll be published later.


### Bug FIxes
* Fixed an issue where the wrong localization string was used when throwing an exception
* Fixed an issue where argument escaping was ignored in a builder method with the ``escape`` bool paramter.</PackageReleaseNotes>
        <PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>true</PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>
        <PackageLicenseFile>LICENSE.txt</PackageLicenseFile>
        <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>
        <PackageVersion>0.4.0</PackageVersion>
        <PackageTags>shell, cli, process, wrapping, commandline,</PackageTags>
        <EmbedUntrackedSources>true</EmbedUntrackedSources>
    </PropertyGroup>

    <PropertyGroup Condition="'$(GITHUB_ACTIONS)' == 'true'">
        <ContinuousIntegrationBuild>true</ContinuousIntegrationBuild>
    </PropertyGroup>
    
    <ItemGroup Condition="'$(TargetFramework)' == 'netstandard2.0' OR '$(TargetFramework)' == 'netstandard2.1'">
        <PackageReference Include="AlastairLundy.Extensions.Runtime" Version="[2.1.0, 3.0.0)" />
        <PackageReference Include="AlastairLundy.Extensions.Processes" Version="[5.5.0, 6.0.0)"/>
    </ItemGroup>

    <ItemGroup>
        <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.SourceLink.GitHub" Version="8.0.0" PrivateAssets="All"/>
    </ItemGroup>
    
    <ItemGroup>
      <Content Include="..\..\LICENSE.txt">
        <Link>LICENSE.txt</Link>
          <PackagePath>LICENSE.txt</PackagePath>
          <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      </Content>
      <Content Include="..\..\README.md">
        <Link>README.md</Link>
          <PackagePath>README.md</PackagePath>
          <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      </Content>
    </ItemGroup>
    
    <ItemGroup>
      <EmbeddedResource Update="Internal\Localizations\Resources.resx">
        <Generator>ResXFileCodeGenerator</Generator>
        <LastGenOutput>Resources.Designer.cs</LastGenOutput>
      </EmbeddedResource>
    </ItemGroup>
    
    <ItemGroup>
      <Compile Update="Internal\Localizations\Resources.Designer.cs">
        <DesignTime>True</DesignTime>
        <AutoGen>True</AutoGen>
        <DependentUpon>Resources.resx</DependentUpon>
      </Compile>
    </ItemGroup>
    
    <ItemGroup>
      <Folder Include="Urls\" />
    </ItemGroup>

</Project>
